records.addlTxt: Court calls 16CM117 & 16CM251 @ 10:12 am. Defendant Andrew A. Eulrich in court with attorney Gary Stephen Dodge.  Elizabeth R. Constable appeared for the State of Wisconsin. State gives plea agreement, DRI, 16CM251, 16CM117 plea already entered, withheld sentence 12 months probation, cost, DNA surcharge, No violent or abusive contact with B.P or K.E. AODA, Counseling deemed by agent.  Plea questionnaire and waiver of rights filed.  Def. understands charge and penalties.  16CM117 Battery, no contest plea.  DRI 16CM251. Def. advised of constitutional rights & J.T. rights.  Def. understands elements.  Atty Dodge is satisfied.  Court finds plea is freely & voluntarily given.  Factual basis stipulated.  Court finds factual basis, accepts plea and finds def. Guilty to Battery in ct 1.  State gives sentencing recommendations. Atty Dodge joins in States recommendation. Def. has nothing to say.  16CM117 Court orders withheld sentence 12 months probation, costs, 200 DNA Surcharge and sample, No violent or abusive contact with B.P. or K.E. Domestic abuse assessment and follow through,  counseling deemed by agent.  Credit for 3 days if revoked.  If probation is revoked or discharged with outstanding financial obligations, a civil judgment shall be entered, without further order of the court, against the defendant in favor of restitution victims and/or governmental entities for the balance due.  All available enforcement actions will be used to collect the debt.  Def. advised of postconviction rights. Court deems agreement revoked.  Court is finding def. Guilty to ct as charge w/enhancer.
Review hearing on March 31, 2017 at 01:00 pm.

Defendant Andrew A. Eulrich in court.  Galen Bayne-Allison appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Court reviews court record.  Statement by Atty Bayne-Allison.  Agreement reached. Deferred prosecution agreement.  Court reviews agreement, bond will continue with conditions.   If complies with agreement, will be dismissed  Review hearing scheduled for March 30, 2017 at 01:00 pm.
Judicial Pretrial - in court on September 26, 2016 at 03:15 pm.

Defendant Andrew A. Eulrich in court.  Galen Bayne-Allison appeared for the State of Wisconsin.   Court reviews court record.  Def has applied for court appointed atty, court has denied.  Def indicates he will represent himself.  Not guilty plea entered.  Def to make an appointment with DA's office.  Bond will continue with condition  Status conference scheduled for September 12, 2016 at 04:00 pm.
